                                                        <p>And, user documentation isn’t just for new users. </p>

                                                        <p>Experienced customers may also refer to user manuals or product guides to refresh their memories on a feature they haven’t used often or to solve a specific problem they may have.&nbsp;</p>

                                                        <p>For this post, we&#8217;ll focus mostly on best practices for creating user documentation for non-physical products such as software, but most if not nearly all of these tips also apply to the physical product realm.&nbsp;</p>

